Quote: We'd heard tales from blokes who had,[worked in the North Island] of punching big mobs of romneys, the predominance of huntaways and beauty of Maori women. Mustering for Gordon Lucas through Tarras way, punching 2000 lambs short of water, getting in the river, I was generally having a hard day of it.
